quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  7,58,"And the good land -- its vegetation comes forth by the leave of its Lord, and the corrupt -- it comes forth but scantily. Even so We turn about the signs for a people that are thankful"
  7,59,"And We sent Noah to his people; and he said, 'O my people, serve God! You have no god other' than He; truly, I fear for you the chastisement of a dreadful day"
  7,60,"Said the Council of his people, 'We see thee in manifest error"
  7,61,"Said he, 'My people, there is no error in me; but I am a Messenger from the Lord of all Being"
  7,62,"I deliver to you the Messages of my Lord, and I advise you sincerely; for I know from God that you know not"
  7,63,"What, do you wonder that a reminder from your Lord should come to you by the lips of a man from among you? That he may warn you, and you be godfearing, haply to find mercy"
  7,64,"But they cried him lies; so We delivered him, and those with him, in the Ark, and We drowned those who cried lies to Our signs; assuredly they were a blind people"
  7,65,"And to Ad their brother Hood; he said, 'O my people, serve God! You have no god other than He; will you not be godfearing"
  7,66,"Said the Council of the unbelievers of his people, 'We see thee in folly, and we think that thou art one of the liars"
  7,67,"Said he, 'My people, there is no folly in me; but I am a Messenger from the Lord of all Being"